	)
	(text "7.2.2.1 RMII Layout Guidelines\n1. Remember that RMII signals as single-ended signals.\n2. Traces must be routed with 50Ω impedance to ground.\n3. Keep trace lengths as short as possible. TI recommends to keep the trace lengths between two to six inches\nlong."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 35.814 32.004 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "08902199-0488-4548-aed7-9f2dcb17f947")
	)
	(text "7.2.2.2 MDI Layout Guidelines\n1. Remember that MDI signals are differential.\n2. Traces must be routed with 50Ω impedance to ground and 100Ω differential controlled impedance.\n3. Route MDI traces to the transformer on the same layer.\n4. Use a metal-shielded RJ-45 connector and electrically connect the shield to chassis ground.\n5. Avoid supplies and ground beneath the magnetics.\n6. Do not overlap the circuit ground and chassis ground planes. Keep chassis ground and circuit ground\nisolated by turning chassis ground into an isolated island by leaving a gap between the planes. Connecting\na 1206 (size) capacitor between chassis ground and circuit ground is recommended to avoid floating metal.\nCapacitors less than 805 (size) can create an arching path for ESD due to a small air-gap.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 243.332 36.83 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "83eb44d3-591f-4875-82e5-68d71ade36c1")
	)
